    <td>
      <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center">
        <tr>
          <td bgcolor="#224372">
            <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="4">
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#000000" background="images/forum-cell.gif" colspan="2" align="center"><b><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">T O P I C&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;R E V I E W</font></b></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><b>avrorr</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;11/13/2002&nbsp;: 3:46:31 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Before I get started here I want to make 1 or 2 things clear. I'm not Uber. I dont have crazy gear but it's good enough. I know a lot of necros know way more about POD than I do. <br />Ok now that thats out in the open here we go.<br /><br /><br /><b>Preperation:</b> (I like being safe so some of this you might not find nessasery). <br /><br />1st: Switch out all the gear i can with hp gear.<br /><br />2nd: Get a cleric to aego or a druid to POTG. (I perfer POTG since it has mana regen to it)<br /><br />3rd: check peridots and make sure i have enough to last me the night.<br />(usually 5)<br /><br />4th: Get set up in POT right at POD zone in. buff up. dmf/shild/manaskin (reason i do it in POT and not at graveyard is becuase people train there a lot).<br /><br />Now that you're  all set invis up and zone in.<br /><br /><br /><b>Getting to camp spot:</b><br /><br />Camp 1: When you zone in head straight out to the watter and to your left. I really dont recomand this spot since the mobs here at high lvl. oger guy spawns nearby that red to me and masquito things that are yellow that dot/root/snare/nuke. The only reason why I mention this spot is becuase there is plenty of fearable rats here.<br /><br />camp 2: face the watter. hug the left wall and go. when u get to a pile of rocks stop. this is camp spot. pull rats mostly. Although this spot is near zone it not a great spot to hunt in. Favorit hunting grounds for druids/rangers soloing. and where most of traines are run through. <br /><br />camp 3: Now this one is a good spot. zone in. hug the wall to yoru left when facing the watter. keep going untill u see spider. back out so you right at the spider entrance. back up to the direction that you were coming from a little away from entrance so you're not in the way of the one wondering spider and the goo. set up pet. turn taunt off. make sure your back is to the wall in run straight out. you'll see enough to pull. bring it back to pet. fear it and you know the rest. By the way u dont have to chase the mob. just sit and med. refresh fear/dot/snare.<br /><br /><br />camp 4: Keep the best for last right?. I dont know if this is the best but I like this spot a lot. plenty of room to kite if fear doesn't stick. no roamers. and if you can ever find the CY uncamped or even camped and feel like taking a risk you can always pull an underbulk or a lightcrawler. As you probably guessed it this is in front of the castle/courtyard. Facing the gate to go into the yard, turn left and go left just enough where you wont be getting trained by groups not able to handle thier pulls in courtyard. run straight out and you'll see a ton of goo's and rats to pull. if you dont see anything over the hill wait there a few secs something will crawl out of the watter. if you go out to far to pull and something spawns behind you..well lets just say it's not good, not good at all.<br /><br /><br /><b>Mobs:</b><br /><br />1) light crawlers. (blue to lvl 57 and nothing above even con)<br /><br />a: A desised light crawler. (this guys resist like hell at 57)<br />b: A light crawler pest. (easiest of the three)<br />c: A light crwaler defiler. (this is the hardes one if u ask me. He HT's on pull. resists like hell. casts or not sure if procs fear and dots.<br /><br />2) Underbolks: (blue to yellow at 57) Three ypes of these just as the crawlers. safe characteristics. Although I admit i dont have much experiance with these.<br /><br />3) Goos and Bials: (The ones I have fough have all been blue and fearble) There is a named one that spawns if your pulling at camp 4 but haven't killed him yet. was blue to me and was in a middle of a pull so couldn't get him and by the time i got back it was gone.<br /><br />4) Rats: Easy pulls just like th goos. feable rats all ahve been fearable. pesteline rats ahve all reisted fear. swamp rats = uber rats. I dont touch those. <br /><br />5) Spiders: never again will i touch one of these.<br /><br />6) Magus deathbons (caster mobs in front of castle). This are undead but wouldn't recomand doing them unless you ahve a partner. these con blue to yellow and nuke in the 900's. dot. malis. Not a hard mob to take down but again wouldn't recomand it solo at 57. They resist 3 out of 4 casts.<br /><br />7) all other. all the other mobs I have not touched yet. So sorry for lack of info.<br /><br /><b>spell lign up:</b><br /><br />Darkness<br />Fear<br />Deflux<br />Vexing<br />splurt/coc<br />lich<br />harmshild<br />FD<br /><br /><br /><b> Tactics:</b> All necros at this point should know both how to fear kite and how to agro kite. If u dont sorry but POD is not a place to practice. With pet tunt off it's very easy to keep agro on unfearable mobs by just casting fear. I know there was sugestions to use monk pet but I use the roug pet. I love the BS and if you time your snare and fears right you will never have a problem. On light crawlers. Dooming, splurt and 8 casts of fear will gain enough agro for the whole fight. When fear kiting, I pull with darkness. get back to pet and refresh darkness and fear. at 20% health loss of the mob I recast fear. at 40% loss resnare. 60% loss of health fear again and at 80% dooming again. pet never gets hit when doing this.<br /><br /><br /><b>XP</b><br /> xp doens't always seem to be the same and although I can't exactly tell you how much xp per kill it is,  i avrage about 6-8 blues an hour pulling non stop. Too me thats good might not be for all. AA moves a lot faster. way faster than xp. with 10% going to AA the time it took me to get 1 yellow of xp i had about 4 1/2 of blue into AA.<br /><br /><br /><b>Notes</b><br /><br />Some things that might be of interest.<br />Resists on goos is very low if any. I might get maybe 1 resist of dooming per 10 mobs. Dont get me wrong there are those that will resist 4 or 5 in a row but in general no resists.<br />If You dont ahve run 2 or better (including some type of sow) dont bother. too much to risk. You get 2 or 3 resists and you're dead.<br />camp 4 mentioned above being my fave is almost never camped. someone might roam by and set up nearby but they will be far enough and you can prety much see whatever they are doing, how many mobs they ahve, etc etc. <br />With buffs I'm end up with about 2800hp. (if anyone cares)<br /><br /><br /><br />Well this is the end of the guide and hope it helps someone. Keep in mind again that this guide is based off me being in the zone only 2 times. Like my opening said I'm sure someone knows the zone or can put a better guide togethere so if you're going to give me shit dont. I would also appricate anyone adding to this and sharing thier view. I wrote this at work or I would have made crappy drawings of the spots and would have given locs. duoing with any class while fear kiting is very fun. I perfer a mage with thier roug pet, haste mask, nukes and COTH if shit hits the fan on pulls.<br /><br />Dont mind the spelling or grammer mistakes please and enjoy.<br /><br />EDIT: Just read through my post and there is one more thing I wanted to mention. When pulling crawlers from CY to camp 4 or out of CY be carefull. The entrance/exit to CY is buggy and  mobs kind of warp through it one sec they are on your left side walkign straight at you next step they are behind you hitting you for 380's.<br /><br />&lt;a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=284110"&gt;-Avrorr De`Morte-&lt;/a&gt;<br />-57 Defiler-<br />-Master of ALL trades-<br /><br /><br />Edited by - avrorr on 11/13/2002  15:50:27<br /><br />Edited by - avrorr on 11/13/2002  15:59:27<br /><br />Edited by - avrorr on 11/14/2002  08:50:43<br /><br />Edited by - avrorr on 11/14/2002  13:46:27</span></font></td>
