                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/02/2002&nbsp;: 10:49:46 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I've spent a lot of time in PoD and think it owns for pre-tagged PoP exp and OK parch drops.<br /><br />Way down the back of the courtyard behind all the underbulks there are safe spots to both sides of the castle (invis to one of the corners against the castle wall down back). <br /><br />Pull with doom (or epic) and aggro kite or (if you are level 62+ and have upgraded root) pull and root DoT. Decent exp and some parch drops. Only pull defilers if you are close to max health because as mentioned above they HT for a messy 911 or so and cast dots. I generally apply the following if root dotting: Doom x3 or 4 Dark Plague x2 Splurt x2 Pyro x2 Saryns Kiss x1 or 2. The underbulks can heal when low on health so stay close to them (it seems to prevent healing) and if mana permits mujaki or neurotoxin the critter a death blow.<br /><br />Killing underbulks here is pretty dull solo once you are into the swing of things. It owns with 2 or more necros or some mages if you aggro kite (exp flows in). However due to boredom i came up with a new plan........the next hunting spot I mention is not for the faint of heart and as yet is untested. I will check it out tonight as i'm now in position. This is INSIDE the castle.<br /><br />Walk up to near the undead deathbones invis to avoid CY mobs but keep in mind deathbones see invis. When just out of their aggro range cast a harmshield and run through the doors (might need the free tag you get at zone in from PoT for this) up 3 flights of steps and all the way to the top. <br /><br />There are 3 sets of 2 deathbones on route and they'll be nuking your ass hard so ensure resist gear is on for when HS wears off (which is roughly when you hit the top level if you have SoW). Once at the very top of the stairs run between the 2 top deathbones and head right. Then keep running around the corner to the end and FD (seems like a safe spot to me). /q and return as the deathbones will have left by then. I resisted about 3 castings with 200 fire resist BTW - fire seems to be their preferred modus operandi.<br /><br />Next step is to head around to where Gryme hangs out - there are 2 Crypt guardians (level 60 or so non caster mobs) at the base of the stairs. I haven't tried this yet but the theory is to pull with shackle or SoT and FD split these guys then root dot or aggro kite one at a time. <br /><br />This promises to be pretty challenging I think - i'll let you know how it goes :) I DO know this much - a full group gets awesome exp here pulling crypt guardians + deathbones and slowing them for tankage. They definitely drop parchments (just ethereal so far). You definitely can't root them if you don't have upgraded roots (I tried at level 61 and it broke WAY too fast). They are definitely snareable, mezzable and slowable.<br /><br />Oh and watch out for Gryme if pulling these guys - if you aggro him he'll own you so fast you won't know what hit you :P (Though he can be killed with 2 solid teams....)<br /><br />NB I am non uber - no epic - no FP - no level 61 pet (yet). However, I am certifiably insane and like to push the limit - death doesn't deter me one bit.<br /><br />Looking forward to trying this out having already lived through the run to the camp spot.<br /><br />Falrinth<br />62 Warlock<br />Cazic Thule</span></font></td>
