                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;11/20/2002&nbsp;: 2:56:38 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Ok, I(58 necro) hunted on left side of the castle with my brother who is a 60 druid(I know, but there was no one else :P )<br /><br />We duoed the underbulks and it was pretty easy. Even with him I was getting 1% of regular XP on some kills and less than 1% on others. I would think that you may get like .75% per kill based on my experience.<br /><br />I found a great area for aggro kiting. If you face the castle while in front and you follow it around to the left, set up camp at the back of the zone, right next to the castle.<br /><br />if you pull and run up and down the castle wall, the mob runs parallel to you and as long as you run to the other side before it makes the turn to get you, you are safe. <br /><br />If this an exploit, hmm.. maybe, not sure, but the mob CAN get to you if you dont move away from it when it come close to you, so it may be a little iffy.<br /><br />One thing though, make sure you keep Dooming Darknees up. The times that I have died have been because it either ran out or was resisted and them ran out.<br /><br />BTW, I used a rogue pet and waited until the mob had lost 10% health before I sent him in. I also had tghe level 4 fear spell memmed in case it turned on the pet.<br /><br />Watch out when the mob enrages, it can tear through your pet in seconds. When mob hits about 10% it stops moving and I back pet off a bit to see if it is going to enrage. If it enrages, then I wait until it's done and then send pet back in. If it doesn't enrage, then I let pet finish it off.<br /><br />thanks<br /><br /></span></font></td>
